               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors ; groups of lines on the incipit page of Text I-1, incipit of sections and of subsections; the word täfäśśǝḥi “rejoice” in Text I-2; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-1 includes excerpts from Säʿatat zä-lelit “Horologium for the Night” (fols. 5va-6rb, with the hymn:</note>
                     <note>Sälam läki ḫoḫǝtä mǝśraq... “Salutation to you, Threshold of the East…”, fol. 6ra).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-3 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝlt bä-kǝlʾe Maryam... "O my Holy Lady Mary and Two-fold Virgin..." (fol. 8rb-va)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Maryam ʾǝmmu lä-ʾIyäsus Krǝstos kähali... "O my Lady, Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ, the Almighty..." (fol. 8va-) (cp. ChRep no. 373)</note>
                     <note>- Sälam läki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Maryam ʾǝmmä mädḫǝn wä-ʾǝmmä bǝrhan... "Salutation to you, o my Lady Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the Light..." (fols. 8va-9ra).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The miracles of Text I-4 are numbered.</note>
                  </msItem>
